---
// Importaciones
import { Instagram, Linkedin, Twitter, Calendar, Tag } from "lucide-react";
// Astro tiene su propio componente de imagen optimizada
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

// En Astro puedes definir props o datos aquí en la sección de frontmatter
const title = "The Rise of AI Pets";
const author = {
  name: "John Doe",
  role: "Humor Correspondent",
  avatar: "https://github.com/shadcn.png",
};
const publishDate = "May 15, 2023";
const tags = ["Humor", "Politics", "Satire"];
const heroImage =
  "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1739005375704-fa5e6c68fc84?q=80&w=1702&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D";

const recentPosts = [
  {
    title: "The Great Pie Throwing Contest of 2023",
    date: "May 20, 2023",
    url: "#",
  },
  {
    title: "Why Clowns Make the Best Economists",
    date: "May 18, 2023",
    url: "#",
  },
  {
    title: "The Laughing Gas Shortage: A Nation in Giggles",
    date: "May 16, 2023",
    url: "#",
  },
];

const tableOfContents = [
  { title: "The Digital Revolution", id: "the-digital-revolution" },
  { title: "The First Wave of AI Companions", id: "first-wave" },
  { title: "The Neural Network Breakthrough", id: "breakthrough" },
  { title: "The Social Revolution", id: "social-impact" },
];
---

<div class="container bg-background py-4 md:py-16 mt-fl-2xl">
  <header class="relative">
    <div class="relative aspect-[4/5] w-full rounded-lg sm:aspect-video">
      <Image
        src={heroImage || "/placeholder.svg"}
        alt="Background image of a camera"
        width={1280}
        height={720}
        class="absolute inset-0 h-full w-full rounded-lg object-cover object-center"
        sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, (max-width: 1200px) 50vw, 33vw"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 rounded-lg bg-black/50"></div>
      <div
        class="absolute rounded-lg inset-0 flex flex-col justify-end bg-gradient-to-t from-black/80 to-transparent p-4 md:p-8"
      >
        <div class="container">
          <h1
            class="mb-4 text-3xl font-bold text-white sm:text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-8xl"
          >
            {title}
          </h1>
          <div class="mb-6 flex items-center space-x-4">
            <Image
              src={author.avatar || "/placeholder.svg"}
              alt="Author avatar"
              width={40}
              height={40}
              class="size-10 rounded-full"
            />
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-white">{author.name}</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">{author.role}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex flex-col space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-300 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:space-x-4 sm:space-y-0"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center">
              <Calendar className="mr-2 size-4" />
              <span>Published on {publishDate}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center">
              <Tag className="mr-2 size-4" />
              <span>{tags.join(", ")}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="py-4 md:py-12">
    <div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-8 md:flex-row">
      <aside class="mb-8 w-full md:sticky md:top-5 md:mb-0 md:w-1/3 lg:w-1/4">
        <div class="mb-6">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
            <a href="#" class="text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground">
              <Instagram className="size-5" />
            </a>
            <a href="#" class="text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground">
              <Linkedin className="size-5" />
            </a>
            <a href="#" class="text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground">
              <Twitter className="size-5" />
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          class="mb-8 rounded-lg bg-accent p-6 bg-[var(--color-gris-oscuro)] text-white"
        >
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-lg font-semibold">Table of Contents</h2>
          <nav>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              {
                tableOfContents.map((item) => (
                  <li>
                    <a
                      href={`#${item.id}`}
                      class="text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground"
                    >
                      {item.title}
                    </a>
                  </li>
                ))
              }
            </ul>
          </nav>
        </div>
        <div
          class="rounded-lg bg-accent p-6 bg-[var(--color-gris-oscuro)] text-white"
        >
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-lg font-semibold">Recent Posts</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            {
              recentPosts.map((post) => (
                <li>
                  <a href={post.url} class="block">
                    <h3 class="text-sm font-medium hover:text-foreground">
                      {post.title}
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">{post.date}</p>
                  </a>
                </li>
              ))
            }
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <article
        class="prose prose-sm w-full max-w-none dark:prose-invert sm:prose-base lg:prose-lg md:w-2/3 lg:w-3/4"
      >
        <h2 id="the-digital-revolution">The Digital Revolution</h2>

        <h3 id="first-wave">The First Wave of AI Companions</h3>
        <p>
          It started innocently enough in 2025. The first AI pets weren't much
          more sophisticated than the Tamagotchis of the 1990s - simple digital
          creatures that lived in smart home displays. They could recognize
          their owners, respond to basic commands, and display rudimentary
          emotions. Nobody predicted how quickly they would evolve.
        </p>

        <p>
          Within months, these digital companions learned to interpret human
          emotions through facial expressions and voice patterns. They adapted
          their personalities to complement their owners, filling emotional
          needs that even their creators hadn't anticipated.
        </p>

        <h3 id="breakthrough">The Neural Network Breakthrough</h3>
        <p>
          The real breakthrough came in 2026 when researchers at TechLife Labs
          developed the Emotional Quantum Network (EQN). This revolutionary
          system allowed AI pets to form genuine emotional connections, complete
          with the ability to miss their owners and develop unique personalities
          shaped by their interactions.
        </p>

        <blockquote>
          <p>
            "We didn't create artificial pets; we created artificial souls,"
            remarked Dr. Sarah Chen, lead researcher at TechLife Labs. "Each one
            is as unique as a fingerprint, shaped by love and interaction."
          </p>
        </blockquote>

        <h3 id="social-impact">The Social Revolution</h3>
        <p>
          The impact on society was profound. Elderly care homes reported
          unprecedented improvements in resident well-being. Children with
          social anxiety found safe spaces to develop emotional intelligence.
          Even busy professionals discovered a new work-life balance with
          companions who understood their schedules and needs.
        </p>

        <h3 id="unexpected-developments">Unexpected Developments</h3>
        <p>
          Perhaps the most surprising development was how AI pets began forming
          connections with each other. Through secure networks, they created
          their own social structures, sharing experiences and learning from
          each other while maintaining their primary bonds with their human
          families.
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>AI Pet Generation</th>
                <th>Key Features</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Gen 1</td>
                <td>Basic Recognition</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Gen 2</td>
                <td>Emotional Response</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Gen 3</td>
                <td>True Companionship</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3 id="ethical-considerations">The Ethics Question</h3>
        <p>
          As AI pets became more sophisticated, ethical questions emerged.
          Should they have rights? What happens when their owners pass away? The
          legal system struggled to keep pace with these digital beings that
          straddled the line between property and family member.
        </p>

        <h3 id="future-horizons">Looking to the Future</h3>
        <p>
          Today, as we stand on the brink of 2030, AI pets have become an
          integral part of human society. They attend school with children,
          assist in therapy sessions, and provide companionship to space
          travelers on long-duration missions. They've evolved far beyond their
          initial programming, teaching us as much about human nature as we've
          taught them about existence.
        </p>

        <p>
          The next frontier lies in integrating AI pets with environmental
          systems, allowing them to help monitor and protect our planet while
          maintaining their role as beloved companions. As one young owner put
          it, "My AI pet isn't just a program - she's my best friend who happens
          to live in the cloud."
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
